oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Tennessee State University
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Frances E. Thompson, a Faculty Member of Tennessee State University From 1923 to 1969 Created Artistic Designs For All the Programs For Special Occasions and the Various Publications of Tennessee A. & I. During the 1920's and 1930's. The Most Enduring of Her Works, is the School's Seal Which She Designed in 1924, the Same Year the Institution Become Tennessee A. & I. State Teachers College.
